headline: 2 Reasons to Watch GE and 1 to Stay Cautious
summary: Since March 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 126%. But one standout stock has nearly doubled the market - over the past five years, GE Aerospace has surged 232% to $191.86 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 13.1% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 12.9%.
